'''Johny Placide''' (born 29 January 1988) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Ligue 2]] club [[SC Bastia|Bastia]]. Born in France, he plays for and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] since 2011.

==Club career==
Placide began his career on youth side with [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] and was promoted to the first team in July 2008 and played four games in his first season. He played in his debut match on 26 April 2009 against [[Grenoble Foot 38|Grenoble]].<ref>[http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/feuilleMatch.asp?saison=2008/2009&code_evt=D1&code_jr_tr=J33&num_ordre=2 French Football League – Johny PLACIDE]{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

Placide joined [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in January 2013. He made his league debut for the club on 19 January 2013 in a 1–0 away defeat to [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/19/france/ligue-1/fc-sochaux-montbeliard/stade-de-reims/1286218/|title=Sochaux vs. Reims – 19 January 2013|website=Soccerway|access-date=26 January 2019}}</ref> In July 2016, Placide was released from the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stade-de-reims.com/johny-placide-nest-plus-remois/|title=Johny Placide n'est plus rémois|language=fr|website=stade-de-reims.com|date=7 July 2016|access-date=26 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160710003604/http://stade-de-reims.com/johny-placide-nest-plus-remois/|archive-date=10 July 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He went on to play one season for [[En Avant Guingamp|Guingamp]].

On 31 August 2017, Placide signed a two-year contract with [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2017/august/31082017-placide-signs/|title=SIGNING: Latics Sign International Goalkeeper|access-date=31 August 2017|language=en-gb}}</ref> On 26 September 2017, he made his debut for Oldham Athletic in a 3–2 victory over [[Peterborough United F.C|Peterborough United]]. He made several important saves and was awarded the man of the match award for his performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2017/september/28092017-johny-placides-debut/|title=VIDEO: Johny Placide's Debut|access-date=1 October 2017|language=en-gb}}</ref> On 3 October 2017, Placide earned his first clean sheet for Oldham Athletic in a 1–0 victory over [[Crewe Alexandra F.C. Academy|Crewe Alexandra]] in the [[EFL Trophy]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2017/october/03102017-crewe-alexandra-vs.-oldham-athletic/|title=MATCH REPORT: Wellens Makes It Three Wins From Three|access-date=4 October 2017|language=en-gb}}</ref> On 17 April 2018, he saved a key penalty from [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]]'s [[Joe Rafferty]] to help his side secure a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43707329 |title=Rochdale 0-0 Oldham |publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 April 2018 |access-date=24 April 2018}}</ref>

On 5 June 2021, Placide signed for newly-promoted [[Ligue 2]] club [[SC Bastia|Bastia]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|date=5 June 2021|title=Le portier Johny Placide s'engage pour 2 saisons|url=https://www.sc-bastia.corsica/actualites/20212022/equipe-premiere/le-portier-johny-placide-sengage-pour-2-saisons|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Sporting Club Bastia|language=fr|archive-date=31 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220731225258/https://www.sc-bastia.corsica/actualites/20212022/equipe-premiere/le-portier-johny-placide-sengage-pour-2-saisons|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
Placide played for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] at the 2008 Olympic Qualifying Tournament, losing all three qualifying games, but was most fondly remembered for his performance against Mexico; despite losing 5–1, Placide had saved several clear opportunities from Mexico during the match, including a penalty. Despite Placide's heroics, this game eliminated both teams and cost Hugo Sánchez his post as national coach. Placide was then called to the French U21 side playing at the Toulon Tournament. He earned his first French U21 cap in a 1–0 victory over Portugal.<ref>[http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/festival-foot-espoirs/match-festival-foot.php?&match=07 Festival Foot Espoirs Toulon] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090608114721/http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/festival-foot-espoirs/match-festival-foot.php?&match=07 |date=8 June 2009 }}</ref> Placide played his first game for the French U21 squad on 11 February 2009 against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]].<ref>[http://www.fff.fr/selections/espoirs/der_sel_esp/cvjoueurs/527319.shtml Johnny Placide at FFF : sélections, football, fiche, espoirs, féminines, masculines]</ref>

Placide was called up by Haiti for the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], in which his side won [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup Group B|group B]] and made it to the semi-finals for the very first time, before being eliminated by [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].

